<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&message.id=5240#M5240">27</a> of 109
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 539 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I just really do not understand the desire to have vastly improved heals.&nbsp; In the 4 years of leveling a shaman to 70 , I have never felt that this was my prime spot in a grp.&nbsp; Clerics and druids can have that little niche for all I care.&nbsp; To me, I have always been a backup healer, who buffs the party, debuffs/slows the mob and provides some dps through DoT's and rains.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally I'd rather see a improvement in our buffing,debuffing, and slowing over healing; spirit of the leopard and panther were a very good step in the right direction as far as DPS.&nbsp; If the re-envisionment goes through with the proposed changes in improving druid and shaman healing , then all that is accomplished is shoving us into a niche that is already overcrowded (talking about #'s of players in those classes, not # of classes).&nbsp; Improve on what the shaman class is good at, don't make us good at something that 2 other classes already do just fine.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Making shaman able to main heal for extended periods of time in places like RS+ would , in my mind, &nbsp;just bring more of a outcry from druids and clerics.&nbsp; I can already heal for short amounts of time in mpg and can heal in RS for a very short time in RS.&nbsp; To me this seems about right on par with what our design should be.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now , people can say that slow was to powerful.&nbsp; Well don't punish the shamans for the fact that chanters and bst's have slow also.&nbsp; Do something that makes us stand out and be wanted in that aspect.&nbsp; Improvements in healing will not benifit shamans in getting groups.&nbsp; Sure a grps survivability will increase , but honestly will anyone say ' hey lets get a shaman into our grp so that they can heal..'&nbsp; Somehow I just don't thinks those words will ever be typed.&nbsp; Will be more like ' Crap, no druids or clerics lfg , wanna risk getting a shaman as a healer or just call it guits...'</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Groups need a reason to want a shaman, I just don't think that that reason should be based on our ability to heal.&nbsp; I personally don't want to just turn into ' click heal 1 when tank is at x % health, click fast heal if tank is at y% health... repeat for 2 hours then rebuff.....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now as for raids (50+ people).. It does really suck to feel that a shaman is only brought out to buff and then is kinda left out of the action until the raid has reached the named mobs of wherever the raid is at.&nbsp;Trash dies to fast to have any real merit to slowing and debuffing. &nbsp;But&nbsp; we each have our roles, some are just more active than others at certain times during the raid.&nbsp; It still feels good to me that the healers all breathe a sigh of relief when they see my slowed msg come across when we are killing nasty mob X.&nbsp; </DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Sordar <br>lvl 70 shaman<br>D Ro<br><br>javascript:view_profile(626516);
							</div>
								
