	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=4054'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#CC6600;font-weight:bold; '>Veril-Xegony</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Master<br>
			
				Posts: 141<br>
				
				Registered: 03-07-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=4054'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/shaman.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&message.id=5241#M5241">28</a> of 109
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 545 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>First Big Point</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Balancing shaman heals against the fact that shaman can slow is a completely false mechanic that will leave the shaman dramatically underpowered in the main healer role. Attempting to do so will perpetuate the situation of the shaman not being a viable main healer.&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>The summary of my arguement is as follows : Experience groups in current content have a healer and a slower.&nbsp; Clerics and Druids in Muramite Proving Grounds, Ruined City of Drannik, Riftseekers are always healing against the slowed mobs.&nbsp; <BR></DIV>
<DIV>Against trivial content, pretty much any group makeup will work (i.e. nobles causeway, wall of slaughter), monks can tank those zones vs slowed mobs or you can use chain/plate tanks and no slower. <BR><BR>Against the fun and/or more challenging content (i.e. Muramite Proving Grounds, Ruined City of Drannik, Riftseekers) groups <B>require</B> both a dedicated healer and a dedicated slower. One person (Shaman) does not have the spell casting time to be both. Attempting to have a shaman do both makes every fight being a desperate scramble to survive, and in cases of a resisted slow, there is no time to do anything other than spam heal and <B>hope</B> to keep up with the damage. <BR><BR>My dedicated slower and healer roles above are expected to bring other things to the groups - depening on their class, I'm not saying that someone just heals or just slows. <BR>Each of the priests should be able to heal the content, with somoene else doing the slow, and in addition they should bring something extra to the group. <BR>Shaman bring the weakest HP buff, the best melee buffs (a vast array of those to be fair) and Slow.<BR>Druids bring a better HP/AC buffs than shaman - but still lots worse than clerics, mana regen for the group, some melee buffs, tracking, snare damage shields and some great nukes. <BR>Clerics bring the best HP/AC buffs, spell haste and more ways of casting heals than is sensible, and XP rezz. <BR><BR>Clerics bring less to the group than the other priests in fairness - but that is because their HP/AC buffs and healing and rezzing so outweights the other two priests, this has been deemed a balacing factor. Seriously clerics need to get something else.&nbsp; Mebbi a 500hp heal proc that is cast on the mobs as suggested by cannus or a ward that reduced mob damage by 50% which is cast onto the mob.&nbsp; Casting spells onto mobs is more fun that casting spells onto players.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Second&nbsp;Big Point</STRONG></DIV></DIV>
<DIV>The re-envisigioning message makes specific reference to shaman healing against fully slowable mobs.&nbsp; I have two comments about this, first the quote:</DIV>
<DIV>"In a situation where an NPC is fully slowable, you are a superb healer but against an NPC who cannot be slowed, your healing falls behind.&nbsp;"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>First, I challenge the developers to show me where these fully slowable mobs are in Omens or&nbsp;Dragons (current content), or even in GoD beyond the first couple of zones.&nbsp;<STRONG> There are no fully slowable mobs in this content.</STRONG>&nbsp; Because there are no fully slowable mobs, it's pretty clear that shaman are not superb healers against current content.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Secondly, it's clear that you are referring to old content (i.e&nbsp;old world, luclin, tier 1-3 PoP) because that is the only place fully slowable mobs are found.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Without slowed mobs, a Cleric can be a the sole and functional healer against this content for an XP grouop.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>With slowed mobs&nbsp;a shaman can do the same job as the cleric, being the main healer of the group.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Without slow (from the shaman or one of the other slowing classes)&nbsp;the shaman cannot be the healer in the group against this content, the damage is still too much for an efficient XP group.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>One of the points of this class re-envisigioning is that shaman should be able to be the main healer of a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;I would contend that in the old word content a shaman and a cleric are well balanced against each other as they can do the same job.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>I would further contend tat If shaman healing is properly balanced against fully slowable mobs, it logically follows that it is not balanced against mitigating mobs.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>As there are no fully slowable mobs in the current content, it logically follows that shaman healing is not balanced in the current content.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Based on all of the above:&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>1) groups need someone who is a slower</DIV>
<DIV>2) groups need somoene who is a healer</DIV>
<DIV>3) the slower cannot be the healer for the group</DIV>
<DIV>4) A shaman has slow so can fit role 1) (in fact shaman have the best slow in the game so fit role 1) better than anyone else)</DIV>
<DIV>5) A shaman's healing is not enought for them to for as role 2) when somone else is in role 1)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>and the summation of all of that is</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6) shaman need better healing all of the time.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Third Big Point</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>There is some idea that adding in a stance for a shaman might be a good idea, a stance where&nbsp;shaman trade slowing capability for healing capability - I do not accept in the cast of a shaman that this is&nbsp;a good idea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The current game has shaman in the slowing role and filling in the backup healing role.&nbsp; A goad of this re-envisiging is that shaman should be able to be main healers.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>1) There's no way that any increased slow % will be put into the game, the fact that no mob in the last 2 expansions is slowable demonstrates that the developers consider 75% slow to be overpowered.&nbsp; </DIV>2) If a heal/slow stance maintains the current ratios, then it is clear that it is not enought, therefore it needs to boost the current ratios</DIV>
<DIV>3) if you aren't boosting the slow, then you must boost the heal.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>4) While you are healing, you really cannot be the slower in a group.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>5) if this heal/slow stance is better then it will be used all the time, in which case, why not make it that way all the time, rather than provide an option that is only ever done in one way</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>my conclusions are</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6) shaman need better healing all of the time.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My Experience :&nbsp; my main, Veril, is a 70th shaman on Xegony with 650AA, in Qvic, with 45% healing item and every healing AA, FT31 from AA+items.&nbsp; I can heal in MPG and RS if someone else slows the mob, it's not pretty, it's very exciting, and there is quite a bit of downtime. &nbsp; I cannot be the only healer and slower in the group, every time that happens there are deaths.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Reposted from one of the other threads, this is probably a better palace</DIV></DIV>
