Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&message.id=5243#M5243">30</a> of 109
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 530 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><FONT face=Arial>Hello Shammies! </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>First off let me say i do not play a Shaman . My main is a Paladin. I do have my own ideas on overall game balance and since SOE is struggling as usual with balancing your "slows" vs your "heals" i thought i would offer my opinion. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>Im posting this here because it mostly addresses the Shaman portion of the re-envision and the class discussions is where they asked us to talk about this stuff . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>Now to my proposal which will make some shaman heads explode :</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Remove slows from Shaman spellbook and abilities</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Improve Shaman healing so that they are always 80% healing of a Cleric or equivalent to a druid in their "healing stance" </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Give slows equivalent to beastlord slows to Necromancers (mob ages)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Give slows equivalent to bard slowsor slightly better&nbsp;to Wizards (temporal distortion)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Results (hopefullly):</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Shaman are 2nd best healers in the game and fufill thier PRIMARY role as preist/ healer very well while retaining their strong buffing and some debuffing secondary roles. Shaman would be the most desirable Preist main healer in melee heavy groups due to their buffs and melee enhancing abilities. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Necromancers become as desireable in groups as Beastlords currently are for their slowing role.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Wizzies become more desireable in groups as a viable secondary emergency slower and have something to contribute more utility wise. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
