		" 
			>
			<DIV>Well hey all,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>for the record I do not like the Stance idea..</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lets see here the Stance would provide a bonus to healing and a negative to (Slow?)&nbsp; similar to the Druid Stance which is 25% heal bonus - 50% damage decrease....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Shammy lvl 68 1785 shammy 3.75time 558cost<BR>Druid lvl 68 2420 Druid 3.75time 627cost</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1785 + 25% = 2231 less than Druid original heal..&nbsp; So unless they give us a 50% bonus to heal we can not effectivly main heal..&nbsp; So in my head the Stance thing is a bad idea..</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My only personal gripe with the shammy class that Ive been playing for over 5 years now would be to lower cast time on Malos recast on Turgur's (our flag ship slow)..&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>lol how about a set up like melody for the bards - that we can use for SotP line of spells....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>well all take from this as you will but I for one am against the Stance.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I like to be the most versatile class in the game and do not or ever wanted the main heal spot... personal view mind you..&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>	
