		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
GlowingRune wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>5.&nbsp; essence of concealment changes to improved invis + easier to find ingredients</STRONG></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<DIV>This is obviously for clerics, since they've been asking for it over on their boards for months.&nbsp; I assume this may yield a little bit (probably very little) of plat for enterprising shamans.&nbsp; Otherwise irrelevent now that we have a castable fixed self invis.</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV><STRONG>8.&nbsp; add healing potions to the game</STRONG></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<DIV>Assuming these are alchemist created, see #5.&nbsp; Not especially useful for shamans, but may yield some plat.<BR></DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>I disagree.&nbsp; As is, the only way for classes without a fixed invis to get a self casting fixed invis is from a mage.&nbsp; This item costs nothing more than mana, but is no-rent.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Almost every non-invis class&nbsp;carrys around a number of those unreliable 11pp non-stacking&nbsp;insta-cast invis potions.&nbsp; Also, the self-only fixed-duration invis that shamen now get requires 5 of the least-common droppable runes to get.&nbsp; This is something that other invis classes can pick up at level 50+ in the baz for 25pp.&nbsp; Not all shamen are level 67.&nbsp; Not all 67+ shamen have Spirit Veil.&nbsp; Personaly, I would pay about 300pp for a 10-dose fixed duration invis potion just for the convenience of security and inventory space.&nbsp; Since it's fixed duration, it doesn't even need to be insta-cast.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Druids/Enchanters/Wizzards now have a targetable fixed-duration invis.&nbsp; Draw back - Have to be in group.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mages can now summon a fixed-duration invis item that is reagent free.&nbsp; Draw back - Item is lore and no-rent.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Shamen should be able to create fixed-duration potions.&nbsp; Draw back - Costs involved vs free cast/summon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as the healing potions, I think melee classes would love this.&nbsp; Give them recast times like mod rods so they can't be abused.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
