			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=37685'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/troll.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&message.id=5251#M5251">38</a> of 109
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 440 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Here is my take. (History: playing EQ since it first became available in Europe, playing a 65 necro, a 65 shaman on VS (full elemental flagged), but retired due to server population, and starting a new shaman on the Bertox server.)</DIV>
<DIV>For reference: here is the part about Shaman changes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>Shaman</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>In DoN you received the spells Spirit of the Leopard and Spirit of the Panther.&nbsp; You seem to like these new spells and they have added more desirability for you in groups.&nbsp; We will be extending these into full spell lines so that Shaman of other level ranges can see the benefits from these spells.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>As with Druids, we are looking to increase your healing ability so you can function better as main healer in groups.&nbsp; You folks are a little problematic though, since your healing ability is the function of not just your heals, but your ability to reduce an NPCs damage output through slows.&nbsp; In a situation where an NPC is fully slowable, you are a superb healer but against an NPC who cannot be slowed, your healing falls behind.&nbsp; If we were to just improve your heals, you would quickly outshine any other healer when facing NPCs that can be slowed.&nbsp; So, we are investigating ways to improve your healing ability only in circumstances where an NPC cannot be slowed or you choose not to slow the NPC (for your own strange reasons).&nbsp; These changes will be rolled out at the same time as any druid healing changes to ensure that one class does not eclipse the other. </FONT></P>
<P>Having started a shaman from scratch, again&nbsp;I can't comment to the SotL and SotP spells, but they are highly regarded in the serverwide shaman channel. Personally, I can't wait for my new shaman to start using these spells, or the possible future, lower level versions.</P>
<P>It is stated in the quoted text that our healing ability is a function of slow and healing. It is also stated that against an NPC that cannot be slowed, our healing falls behind. I would state that with an NPC that mitigates slow, our healing falls behind. Therefor, our healing should not only be boosted when the&nbsp;NPCs are unslowed, but also when they are partially&nbsp;mitigating&nbsp;slow. In keeping slow part of the healing function as currently implemented and other classes being able to slow almost as well (due to mitigation), and high chances&nbsp;of one of those classes (enchanters and beastlords)&nbsp;being in the group anyway, Shaman will be left&nbsp;out again.&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>
<P>I would like to ask you to still keep our slows part of the healing function, but give it a less significant factor, or at least calculate in the time required to debuff and slow. The only thing we really shine at at the moment, are the SotL and SotP spells. But due to the mana cost and short duration coupled with active mana regen, it may prove to be very tough to keep&nbsp;healing&nbsp;and&nbsp;keep buffs up.</P>
<P>One thing I am missing in the re-envisioning is what SOE thinks the Shaman class should be like. I would like to see a description.&nbsp;The items&nbsp;posted&nbsp;are possible solutions to the problem, but I don't see what SOE thinks the Shaman's role should be. If SOE thinks a&nbsp;Shaman's role should change, fine, but I'd like to see what SOE's vision is on that.</P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-16-2005</span> <span class=time_text>01:12 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
