			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
MrHamster wrote:<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Camigwen_Huzzah wrote:<BR>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>Hello Shammies! </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>First off let me say i do not play a Shaman . My main is a Paladin. I do have my own ideas on overall game balance and since SOE is struggling as usual with balancing your "slows" vs your "heals" i thought i would offer my opinion. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>Im posting this here because it mostly addresses the Shaman portion of the re-envision and the class discussions is where they asked us to talk about this stuff . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>Now to my proposal which will make some shaman heads explode :</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Remove slows from Shaman spellbook and abilities</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Improve Shaman healing so that they are always 80% healing of a Cleric or equivalent to a druid in their "healing stance" </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Give slows equivalent to beastlord slows to Necromancers (mob ages)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial>*Give slows equivalent to bard slowsor slightly better to Wizards (temporal distortion)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Results (hopefullly):</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Shaman are 2nd best healers in the game and fufill thier PRIMARY role as preist/ healer very well while retaining their strong buffing and some debuffing secondary roles. Shaman would be the most desirable Preist main healer in melee heavy groups due to their buffs and melee enhancing abilities. </DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Necromancers become as desireable in groups as Beastlords currently are for their slowing role.</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Wizzies become more desireable in groups as a viable secondary emergency slower and have something to contribute more utility wise. </DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Ample reasons to have Enchanter+ Shaman in group , Shaman + beastlord, etc . </DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>The only classes you wont stack as well with are the druids and clerics ; the other 2 primary healer classes (kind of as it should be)</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>ok go ahead and tell me im nuts ! </DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>ultimately even if you keep best slower role i think shammies need a boost in healing . ( just so you all know where im coming from ) But i think it would be even better if they were uber healers and just left slowing to others classes ( yeah i guess all the shammy 2 boxers would hate this but im thinking of shammy single played mains here. i guess such a change would make shammy bots less the norm)</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Arial></DIV></FONT><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>I'll bite .. your nuts <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><BR><BR>I'm not a shaman either but a lot of shamans I've talked to consider slowing their pimary role. Never met a shaman who wants their primay role to be healing they just want viable healing.<BR><BR>If you want some fun go on the beastlord forums and suggest they drop their slow ! <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Yeah, he's nuts alright!</P>
<P>So who do you want to invite to your group, a cleric who can heal at 100% efficiency or a cleric who can heal at 80% efficiency?&nbsp; Goodbye to all group invites as we'd be a second rate cleric <STRONG>who&nbsp;can't rez</STRONG>&nbsp;and fulfill no other role.</P>
<P>Besides, if I'd wanted to be a cleric I'd have rolled a cleric!&nbsp; (In fact I did, but I found him boring)</P>
<P>66 Trol Shaman, Luclin</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
