<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&message.id=5257#M5257">44</a> of 109
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 388 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I see several things wrong with what is proposed here. The first of which is that slow is somehow overpowered and the combination of slow and heals can unbalance the game. We have a 75% slow that cast somewhat faster then enchanter 70% slow, but enchanters also get a very fast casting magic debuff with no recast time that is unresistable. enchanters also get the rune line, which i have used on my enchanter many times as a ghetto heal when the healer is down/oom.to the tune of 1500hp heals with a 3 second cast time, in addition to giving them mezes, and promising to improve charm....</DIV>
<DIV>what crutches are&nbsp;planned for this class that was already desireable if not mandatory in all groups??? I would suggest some form of stances for enchanters as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp; Beastlords--- they are a hybrid class with some of the abilities of shaman and some of monk, why is it that they are being given the a more potent heal at a time when our ability to heal is being restricted? unless their "new improved" slow has a 6-10 second cast time, they are also being given a better slow than MOST shaman of the same level, they get a slow with a magic debuff (equal? close?) to malos, without first having to cast a malos. shaman need to use 1 more spell gem, and live with a 5 sec cast debuff before slowing, not to mention the high mana cost of the malos/slow combo vs. the other classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Shaman as a main healer would still require a cleric or paladin within an xp group in the event of a death for purposes of rezing, so as it stands shaman cant even backup heal with a druid main healing unless facing trivial content without a paladin in the group to rez. I would suggest giving either shaman or druids the rez line of spells to correct this.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
