		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>sorry, wasnt quite ready to submit yet,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Seeing as shaman heals are restricted based on a slowed mob, then it wouldnt be overpowering to give us healing capabilities equal to a druid, since we were already able to slow vs. this supposedly slowed mob. the only benefit we would have from improved heals would be in the event that a mob was NOT slowable or mitigated slow, in which case, we would be merely adequate healers. I, like most shaman strive to be only adequate&nbsp;as a secondary healer,&nbsp;I DO NOT want to be main healer in my group. I was happy being called&nbsp;just "slower". But in todays content that is not bringing enough to the table to fit in&nbsp;most xp groups. I would like nothing more then for ALL slows to be&nbsp;re-envisioned (nerfed to an appropriate degree)&nbsp;across the board for all classes, have mitigation removed from the game, and go back to the "good ol' days" when clerics&nbsp;didnt feel threatened by shaman having nearly as powerfull of heals, and druids/shaman competing for groups was a non issue as well. When kunark&nbsp;came out and i got turgur's i felt like (and practically was) a god. I was in a high end raiding guild and had the best of equipment (lol full JB armor). I was soloing content that would take a full group just 5 levels below me&nbsp;if they didnt have a shaman, that was wrong and should have been corrected 4 years ago.&nbsp; That having&nbsp;been the case, still does not excuse&nbsp;the treatment of shaman today. The class is broken, and the current proposals are insufficient to correct even the simplest problems.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>P.S. i am not in a high end raiding guild right now, my shaman is semi-retired and i play enchanter as my main. I do not propose nerfing of slow based on a high end raider.I dont think the class balance should take high end raiders into account, there should be a select few elite zones made to challenge those people, as they earned their gear and deserve to be challenged. But everone else should not be penalized due to their elite status.</DIV>	
