			>
			For me the question is, why did i choose to be a shaman.<br>When i started with eq and read about all the classes a friend told me the shamans are the best slower in eq and have some nice dots to add some dps, furthermore they have some very good buffs to spread.<br>That's why i decided and how i play a shaman, slowing adding a dot or two and buffing. I love it.<br>I am NOT a healer and i never wanted to be one otherwise i would have decided to play a cleric as others said before.<br><br>It should be easier for shamans to solo ? Add a LITTLE love to our pets, some more HPs maybe ?<br>Adding a shaman to a group should be a good choice ? Let them notice a shaman did slow, no need to change all slowing classes, or even remove their slow.<br>A little push to Turgur would do, others slow partially, we do mostly, others do mostly, we do almost completly, something like that.<br><br>With Torpor i was able to solo quite well, even better with Q and Leo, not as good as a BST, but i am no BST so i'm fine with that.<br>With Turgur working better than other slows i don't think we would be able to solo in oow/don since these hard hitting mobs would still kill us easily, after all that's my experience at 65 with no raid equipment.<br>I love to see my group relax a bit after my slow landed on the mob and i hate to be asked if i did slow or see a BST/ENC try to reslow my mob because they are unsure if i did my job.<br>I did and i do my job but they simply don't notice it anymore if i don't tell in group that the mob is slowed.<br><br>In my opinion a minor change to the shammys pet and slow is far better than a major change to the class.<br>I had to experience it in other games and that's why i quit there, they made my tank become a healer and the healer a tank, of course that has been far more drastically than increasing the healing capability of a shaman but still it's the same way in my opinion.<br><br>I'm a backup healer, if thing get worse i can throw out a Q/Torpor and maybe even a Leo for the MT to save the day and i like it that way.<br>I don't want to be elite or an all-in-one class, i don't want to play WoW/EQ2, i want my shammy to be like he was when i decided to play one even in the new worlds.<br>Not a slower but THE slower, not Uber but a good choice for groups like a tank, a mezzer and a healer.<br><br>So a little love to shammy pets, a little push-up to Turgur and for me there's no need to change anything else about a shaman.	
